title: Laura Vainionpää
text:
Laura Vainionpää (born 11 April 1994) is a Finnish <a href="bicycle%20racing">racing cyclist</a>, who currently rides for Belgian amateur team S-Bikes Bodhi Cycling. She rode in the <a href="2016%20UCI%20Road%20World%20Championships%20%E2%80%93%20Women%27s%20road%20race">women's road race</a> at the <a href="2016%20UCI%20Road%20World%20Championships">2016 UCI Road World Championships</a>, but she did not finish the race.
Prior to her cycling career, Vainionpää was also a member of the <a href="Finland%20women%27s%20national%20under-18%20ice%20hockey%20team">Finland women's national under-18 ice hockey team</a> at the <a href="2012%20IIHF%20World%20Women%27s%20U18%20Championship">2012 IIHF World Women's U18 Championship</a>, playing at <a href="Forward%20%28ice%20hockey%29">forward</a>.
Her father <a href="Arto%20Vainionp%C3%A4%C3%A4">Arto</a> and brother <a href="Oskari%20Vainionp%C3%A4%C3%A4">Oskari</a> are also road cyclists.
